long_desc.thetext:
Well, regardless of the removal of file-roller in F26/F26, it's worth checking why the same application behaves differently between Wayland and X11, so I dig it further.

It appears that file-roller keeps changing the sensitivity of its widgets quite often, base on various parameters (batch mode, loading a file, clipboard operation, etc.).

On Wayland, all this works, but once the file is loaded, file-roller will update one last time and this is where it hangs on Wayland, in fr_window_update_paste_command_sensitivity() while trying to get the content of its own clipboard:

  https://git.gnome.org/browse/file-roller/tree/src/fr-window.c#n717

	if (clipboard == NULL)
		clipboard = gtk_widget_get_clipboard (GTK_WIDGET (window), FR_CLIPBOARD);
